 - `x` uses the X API directly with OAuth user-context credentials for home timeline, user posts, mentions, bookmarks, and list posts.
 - `notion` targets the hosted Notion MCP server, so users should authenticate through Notion OAuth instead of pasting a Notion token into OpenWiki.
 - `google` uses the Gmail API directly with OAuth user credentials to fetch recent mail, with room to add Drive, Calendar, and other Google providers later.
+- `discord` runs the local `discrawl` JSON CLI against explicitly approved guilds, channels, or the local-only DM cache.
 - `imessage` runs the fixed local `imsg` command against explicitly approved Messages chats on macOS.
 - `web-search` uses Tavily through LangChain and requires `TAVILY_API_KEY`.
 - `hackernews` uses public Hacker News feed and search APIs, with no credentials required.
 
+### Discord
+
+Discord ingestion reads a local [Discrawl](https://github.com/openclaw/discrawl)
+archive. It never accepts or scrapes a Discord user token. Configure at least
+one explicit scope in `~/.openwiki/connectors/discord/config.json`:
+
+```json
+{
+  "enabled": true,
+  "guildIds": ["123456789012345678"],
+  "channelIds": [],
+  "includeDms": false,
+  "windowHours": 24,
+  "maxMessages": 500
+}
+```
+
+`guildIds` and `channelIds` contain Discord snowflakes. When both are present,
+the selected channels must also belong to a selected guild. `includeDms` is
+off by default because Discrawl DMs come from the local desktop cache. The
+connector caps `windowHours` at 720 and `maxMessages` at 5000, fails closed on
+schedule gaps or truncated queries, keeps a cursor per channel, and writes only
+allowlisted normalized message fields.
+
+Use `discrawl --json channels list` to inspect the archive without copying a
+token into OpenWiki. To keep it current, configure Discrawl separately with a
+supported bot token and grant the bot View Channel and Read Message History in
+the selected channels. Discord may return empty message content unless the bot
+has Message Content intent. For hardened launchd runs, set the absolute CLI
+path in `~/.openwiki/.env`, then run the configured source:
+
+```sh
+OPENWIKI_DISCRAWL_EXECUTABLE=/opt/homebrew/bin/discrawl
+OPENWIKI_WIKI_DIR=/absolute/path/to/wiki openwiki ingest discord --print
+```
+
